CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 2, 1958, pg. A2, reads: "Still Winning - Catherine Wallace, talented lyric soprano, who is studying at the Juilliard School of Music in New York City, has been awarded her fourth scholarship by the school for the coming term (her senior year) and another scholarship for the second time, but the International House, New York. She lives at 316 Hale St. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of singer Catherine Wallace wearing dress with studded or rhinestone neck and corsage of rosebuds, posed clasping hands
